<plot>This program chronicles the ingenious life saving acts of Private John Simpson, a stretcher bearer during World War I, he singlehandedly went into the line of fire and rescued wounded soldiers. When there were no stretchers, Jack got the idea in his head to borrow a donkey to carry the wounded to the base camp.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?271949</url></doc>
